        [
          "When you were younger you ran through the maze of side streets in your home town and even though you were poor and homeless, the endless maze made you happy to be alive.  As you grew up on the streets the charm of the maze wore thin and the draw of narcotics grew stronger.  When the Sabbat found you, they almost passed you up for food but one in their number saw soemthing if use in you still.  As a Nosferatu you were a feared warrior and joined the ranks of Cardine Scorso in Mexico City with pride.  Such a famous pack would only grow your legend.  But soon you became disenchanted.  The Priest spoke strange words and told sermons of Caine you'd never heard before and soon you found the old craving for drugs returning to your dead blood.  Now you no longer wade into combat with joy, but with resignation.  You seek pleasure on your path, but find little comfort outside of pain."
